EThe%20economy%20could%20take%20a%20hit%2C%20with%20industries%20like%20manufacturing%20and%20education%20needing%20to%20replace%20boomer%20workers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThose%20new%20retirees%20will%20likely%20be%20disproportionately%20leaning%20on%20Social%20Security%20to%20stay%20afloat.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20youngest%20baby%20boomers%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-crisis-social-security-poverty-older-americans-savings-inequality-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabout%20to%20enter%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20most%20of%20them%20aren't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-savings-investment-crisis-middle-class-americans-racial-inequality-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancially%20prepared%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20this%20next%20stage%20of%20their%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeginning%20this%20year%2C%20over%2030%20million%20boomers%20born%20from%201959%20to%201964%20will%20start%20to%20turn%2065%2C%20marking%20the%20%26quot%3Blargest%20and%20final%20cohort%26quot%3B%20of%20that%20generation%20entering%20retirement%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.protectedincome.org%2Fpeak65-economic-impact-forum%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Alliance%20for%20Lifetime%20Income's%20Retirement%20Income%20Institute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20cohort%20is%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bpeak%20boomers%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20per%20the%20report%2C%20most%20of%20them%20are%20on%20track%20for%20significant%20economic%20headwinds.%20It's%20what%20some%20have%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-not-enough-retirement-savings-gen-z-millennials-eldercare-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20boomer%20retirement%20bomb%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20might%20be%20costly%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20workers%20in%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20an%20analysis%20of%20data%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%20Health%20and%20Retirement%20Study%2C%20the%20report%20found%20that%2052.5%25%20of%20peak%20boomers%20have%20%24250%2C000%20or%20less%20in%20assets%2C%20meaning%20that%20they'll%20likely%20deplete%20their%20savings%20and%20rely%20primarily%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-benefits-republicans-raise-age-retirement-cuts-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincome%20from%20Social%20Security%20in%20retirement.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Additionally%2C%20another%2014.6%25%20of%20that%20cohort%20have%20%24500%2C000%20or%20less%20in%20assets%2C%20meaning%20%26quot%3Bnearly%20two-thirds%20will%20strain%20to%20meet%20their%20needs%20in%20retirement%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAmerica%20has%20never%20seen%20so%20many%20people%20reaching%20retirement%20age%20over%20a%20short%20period%2C%20and%20well%20over%20half%20of%20them%20will%20find%20it%20challenging%20to%20meet%20their%20needs%20through%20their%20retirements%2C%20let%20alone%20maintain%20their%20current%20standard%20of%20living%2C%26quot%3B%20Robert%20Shapiro%2C%20an%20author%20of%20the%20report%20and%20the%20former%20Under%20Secretary%20of%20Commerce%20for%20Economic%20Affairs%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BThey%20lack%20the%20protected%20income%20that%20many%20older%20Boomers%20have%20from%20solid%20pensions%20or%20higher%20savings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20peak%20boomers'%20retirement%20wave%20could%20also%20impact%20the%20overall%20US%20economy.%20The%20report%20projects%20that%20employers%20will%20have%20to%20replace%20as%20many%20as%2014.8%20million%20peak%20boomers%20%E2%80%94%20primarily%20in%20the%20manufacturing%2C%20healthcare%2C%20and%20education%20industries%20%E2%80%94%20which%20could%20decrease%20economic%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20top%20of%20that%2C%20the%20generation's%20retirement%20is%20likely%20to%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20consumer%20spending.%20Using%20data%20from%20the%20Consumer%20Expenditure%20Survey%2C%20the%20report%20found%20that%20peak%20boomers%20will%20spend%20%24204%20billion%20less%20in%202032%20than%20they%20did%20in%202022%2C%20with%20the%20transportation%20sector%20taking%20the%20biggest%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20as%20the%20report%20noted%2C%20younger%20employees%20are%20likely%20to%20fill%20some%20of%20the%20jobs%20that%20peak%20boomers%20will%20leave%2C%20and%20productivity%20will%20rise%20as%20technology%20advances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20crisis%20is%20partially%20due%20to%20changes%20in%20how%20Americans%20save%20for%20retirement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeak%20boomers%20entered%20the%20workforce%20just%20as%20retirement%20plans%20shifted%20away%20from%20defined%20benefit%20plans%20like%20pensions%20%E2%80%94%20which%20generally%20guarantee%20stable%20income%20and%20are%20employer-subsidized%20%E2%80%94%20to%20defined%20contribution%20plans%20like%20401(k)s%2C%20which%20rely%20on%20workers%20to%20pay%20into%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20report%2C%20out%20of%20the%20different%20types%20of%20retirement%20savings%2C%20defined%20benefit%20pensions%20have%20the%20least%20disparities%20along%20racial%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20ethnicity%20lines%20(although%20annual%20payments%20see%20big%20disparities)%20%E2%80%94%20but%20only%2024%25%20of%20peak%20boomers%20hold%20them%2C%20and%20even%20those%20plans%20are%20coming%20up%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbidens-big-stimulus-bill-helps-pay-pensions-2-years-later-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epotential%20underfunding%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FkmzmM%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Active%20participants%20in%20pension%20plans%5C%22%