eeds%2C%20based%20on%20a%20hierarchical%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20defines%20the%20concept%20as%20being%20economical%20with%20water%20usage%2C%20using%20only%20the%20bare%20minimum%20that%20one%20needs%2C%20and%20not%20as%20much%20as%20is%20abundantly%20available.%20This%20can%20be%20achieved%20by%20two%20principles%3A%20use%20less%20and%20reuse%20more.%20Using%20less%20is%20obvious%20but%20needs%20reminding%20(low%20tap%20flow%2C%20tap%20off%20when%20not%20needed%2C%20no%20running%20water%2C%20and%20no%20leaks).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20next%20question%2C%20%E2%80%9CWould%20you%20bathe%20with%20mineral%20water%3F%E2%80%9D%20emphasises%20the%20second%20part%20of%20her%20formula%20%E2%80%93%20to%20reuse%20more.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20waste%20water%20of%20higher%20purity%20to%20bathe%2C%20yet%20we%20all%20use%20fresh%20water%20out%20of%20a%20tap%20for%20washing%20mops%20or%20rinsing%20dirty%20dishes%20when%20water%20of%20lower%20purity%20works%20just%20as%20easily%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20her%20calculations%2C%20she%20says%20most%20households%20require%20fresh%20water%20for%20only%2030-40%20percent%20of%20their%20needs%2C%20remaining%20water%20needs%20can%20be%20met%20by%20reusing%20this%20water.%20%E2%80%9CWater%20that%20you%20let%20down%20the%20drain%20is%20always%20good%20for%20some%20other%20purpose%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20suggests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20points%20out%20the%20hidden%20sources%20of%20water%20available%20at%20the%20household%20level%3A%20water%20from%20washing%20hands%2C%20rice%2Fpulses%2C%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%2C%20waste%20RO%20water%2C%20water%20from%20defrosting%2C%20and%20washing%20machine%20outlet%20water.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20these%20are%20not%20fit%20for%20drinking%2C%20they%20can%20be%20reused%20for%20other%20purposes%2C%20even%20if%20clear%2C%20cloudy%2C%20soapy%20or%20muddy%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FOdette-1713425943.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ecowaternomics%20framework%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FOdette-1713425943.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FOdette-1713425943-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FOdette-1713425943-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FOdette-1713425943-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FOdette-1713425943-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-347616%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(See%20slide%3A%20Ecowaternomics%20framework)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20Odette%20adds%20that%20while%20you%20use%20fresh%20purified%20water%20for%20drinking%2C%20cooking%2C%20and%20washing%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%2C%20you%20can%20use%20fresh%20tap%20water%20for%20washing%20hands%20and%20face%2C%20brushing%20teeth%2C%20shaving%2C%20bathing%2C%20washing%20clothes%2C%20and%20toilet%20needs.%20Other%20than%20these%20purposes%2C%20you%20can%20reuse%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20every%20one%20litre%20of%20filtered%20water%2C%20RO%20wastes%20three%20litres%20of%20water.%20Sadly%2C%20many%20let%20this%20down%20the%20drain%20but%20it%20is%20still%20clear%20water%20so%20can%20be%20used%20to%20mop%20floors%20and%20wash%20vessels%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CApplying%20the%20hierarchy%20of%20needs%20principle%2C%20I%20cannot%20bring%20myself%20to%20use%20clear%20RO%20waste%20water%20on%20plants%2C%20as%20cloudy%20water%20collected%20from%20washing%20vegetables%2Fdals%20works%20perfectly%20here%20or%20for%20rinsing%20dirty%20dishes%20%E2%80%93%20again%20why%20use%20water%20of%20a%20higher%20purity%20than%20needed!%20I%20use%20the%20rejected%20water%20from%20the%20RO%20for%20mopping%20and%20then%20reuse%20it%20again%20for%20watering%20plants%2C%20possibly%20because%20I%20use%20organic%20cleaners%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20Odette%20makes%20organic%20cleaners%20that%20make%20the%20water%20safe%20to%20reuse.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20place%20of%20toilet%20cleaners%20and%20floor%20cleaners%2C%20I%20use%20homemade%20bio%20enzymes%20that%20can%20be%20used%20to%20clean%20bathrooms%2C%20floors%2C%20and%20disinfect%20fruits.%20I%20reuse%20this%20to%20water%20my%20plants.%20Bio%20enzymes%20are%20beneficial%20for%20plants%20as%20it%20acts%20as%20a%20fertiliser%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FOdette-1-1713426011.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Odette%20claims%20to%20use%20around%201500%20litres%20less%20water%20per%20day%20than%20an%20equivalent%20household.%C2%A0%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FOdette-1-1713426011.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FOdette-1-1713426011-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FOdette-1-1713426011-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FOdette-1-1713426011-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FOdette-1-1713426011-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-347617%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EOdette%20claims%20to%20use%20around%201%2C500%20litres%20less%20water%20per%20day%20than%20an%20equivalent%20household.%C2%A0%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20this%20organic%20cleaner%2C%20Odette%20says%2C%20mix%20three%20parts%20of%20fruit%20peels%20with%20one%20part%20of%20jaggery%20in%2010%20parts%20of%20water%20in%20an%20airtight%20jar%2C%20stirring%20daily%20to%20release%20gas.%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20six%20weeks%2C%20it%E2%80%99ll%20be%20ready%20to%20use.%20It%20also%20leaves%20a%20beautiful%20aroma%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20soapy%20water%20from%20washing%20hands%2C%20washing%20machine%20outlets%2C%20and%20clothes%20can%20be%20used%20to%20flush%20toilets%2C%20washing%20mops%2Fdustbins%2C%20bathrooms%2C%20washbasins%2C%20buckets%2C%20driveways%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20Odette%20advises%20collecting%20cloudy%20water%20from%20washing%20fruits%2C%20vegetables%2C%20rice%20and%20pulses%20to%20be%20used%20for%20rinsing%20dirty%20utensils.%20Lastly%2C%20muddy%20water%20from%20mops%20can%20be%20used%20to%20water%20plants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOdette%20was%20asked%2C%20years%20back%2C%20if%20there%20is%20any%20need%20to%20go%20to%20this%20extreme%2C%20for%20isn%E2%80%99t%20this%20all%20too%20drastic%3F%20%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20all%20do%20more%20of%20this%20now%2C%20future%20generations%20will%20not%20be%20forced%20to%20do%20this%20all%20the%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20had%20replied.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20that%20scenario%20is%20nearer%20than%20anyone%20expected%2C%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNot%20just%20Bengalureans%2C%20but%20saving%20water%20is%20something%20everyone%20across%20cities%20could%20make%20a%20year-round%20habit%20%E2%80%93%20water%20levels%20are%20depleting%20everywhere.%20Why%20wait%20for%20a%20water%20crisis%20to%20start.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20use%20water%20as%20carefully%20as%20